facts.text: Civil Appeal No. 2043 of 1971 filed in Supreme Court.

anchor.surface_text: CIVIL APPELLATE JURISDICTION Civil Appeal No. 2043 of 1971

facts.text: Appeal by certificate from Allahabad High Court judgment dated July 27, 1970 in Writ Petition No. 1701 of 1964.

anchor.surface_text: Appeal by Certificate from the judgment and order dated July 27, 1970 of Allahabad High Court in Writ Petition No. 1701 of 1964-.

facts.text: Appellant is Agricultural Industrial Syndicate Ltd., tenure-holder of large area of land in villages Aithal Buzurg and Bukkanpur, Saharanpur district, Uttar Pradesh.

anchor.surface_text: The appellant, the Agricultural Industrial Syndicate Ltd., is the tenure-bolder of a large area of land in two villages in the district of Saharanpur in Uttar Pradesh, Aithal Buzurg and Bukkanpur.

facts.text: Some of appellant's land declared surplus under U.P. Imposition of Ceiling on Land Holdings Act.

anchor.surface_text: Some of its land have been declared as surplus land under the U.P. Imposition of Ceiling on Land Holdings Act  hereinafter referred to as the Ceiling Act .

facts.text: Appellant appealed order declaring surplus land to District Judge, appeal unsuccessful.

anchor.surface_text: It went in appeal against the order declaring surplus land to the District Judge, but without success.

facts.text: Allahabad High Court partly allowed and partly dismissed appellant's writ petition.

anchor.surface_text: Its writ petition has been partly allowed and partly dismissed by the Allahabad High Court.

facts.text: Supreme Court appeal by special leave directed against latter part of High Court order.

anchor.surface_text: This appeal, by special leave, is directed against the latter part of the order of the High Court.

facts.text: Appellant did not file statement under Section 9 of Ceiling Act.

anchor.surface_text: As the appellant did number file a statement under s. 9, a statement prepared under S. 10

facts.text: Prescribed Authority prepared statement under Section 10 and served on appellant.

anchor.surface_text: As the appellant did number file a statement under s. 9, a statement prepared under S. 10 was served on it.

facts.text: Appellant filed objection to statement under Section 10, indicating plots to retain as ceiling area.

anchor.surface_text: An objection was filed by it. The objection indicated the plots which it wanted to retain as its ceiling area.

facts.text: Prescribed Authority did not wholly accept appellant's choice of plots.

anchor.surface_text: The Prescribed Authority did number accept its choice wholly.

facts.text: Appellant received C.H. Form V under Consolidation Act for land in village Bukkanpur.

anchor.surface_text: After the decision of the Prescribed Authority, it received H. Form V issued under the provisions of the U.P. Con- solidation of Holdings Act

facts.text: Appellant moved review application before Prescribed Authority due to consolidation in Bukkanpur, rejected on September 15, 1962.

anchor.surface_text: A review application was then moved before the Prescribed Authority on the ground of the pendency of companysolidation operations in village Bukkanpur. The application was rejected on September 15, 1962.

facts.text: Village Aithal Buzurg brought under consolidation operations while appeal against Prescribed Authority pending.

anchor.surface_text: While the appeal against the order of the Prescribed Authority was pending, village Aithal Buzurg was also brought under companysolidation operations.

facts.text: Appellant received C.H. Form V under Consolidation Act for plots in Aithal Buzurg.

anchor.surface_text: The appellant received C.H. Form V issued under the Consolidation Act with respect to the plots situate in village Aithal Buzurg.

facts.text: Appellant made application to appellate authority informing of consolidation operations in two villages.

anchor.surface_text: It made an application to the appellate authority informing him of the initiation of companysolidation operations in the two villages.

facts.text: Appellate authority did not take notice of application and decided appeal on merits, did not wholly accept appellant's choice.

anchor.surface_text: It is said that the appellate authority took numbernotice of the application and decided the appeal on merits. The appellate authority also did number accept wholly the choice of the appellant

facts.text: District Judge order dated January 31, 1964 quashed by Supreme Court.

anchor.surface_text: The order of the District Judge, dated January 31, 1964, is quashed

facts.text: High Court accepted appellant's first contention, rejected second.

anchor.surface_text: The first companytention was accepted by the High Court the second was rejected.

facts.text: High Court quashed appellate authority order and directed decision in light of its judgment.

anchor.surface_text: The High Court quashed the order of the appellate authority and directed it to decide the appeal in the light of its judgment.

facts.text: High Court directed stay of proceedings before consolidation authorities until appellate authority decides ceiling appeal.

anchor.surface_text: The High Court also directed that the proceedings before the companysolidation authorities would remain stayed until the appeal was decided

facts.text: Consolidation Officer and Asst. Settlement Officer dismissed objections of persons claiming interest in appellant's plots.

anchor.surface_text: the Consolidation Officer and the Asstt. Settlement Officer had adjudicated upon the objections of a large number of persons claiming interest in the plots of the appellant. Their objections were dismissed.

facts.text: Revisions against dismissal of objections pending when High Court heard writ petition.

anchor.surface_text: They filed revisions against those orders. The revisions were pending when the petition was heard by the High Court.

facts.text: State Government issued notification under Section 6 of Consolidation Act canceling notification bringing villages under consolidation.

anchor.surface_text: After the decision of the High Court, the State Government has issued a numberification under s. 6 of the Consolidation Act canceling the numberification bringing the aforesaid villages under companysolidation operations.

facts.text: High Court admitted appellant's writ petition against Section 6 notification and stayed its operation.

anchor.surface_text: But the High Court has admitted a writ petition of the appellant against this numberification and has stayed the operation of the numberifica- tion.

facts.text: Appellant raised argument for stay of Ceiling Act proceedings during consolidation before Prescribed and appellate authorities.

anchor.surface_text: It is clear from the facts already stated that the appellantdid raise at the proper time before the Prescribed Authority and the appellate authority the argument that the proceedings under the Ceiling Act should remain stayed

facts.text: Large number of persons filed claims to appellant's plots before Consolidation Authorities, pending in revisions under Section 48.

anchor.surface_text: Admittedly a large number of persons have filed claims to the plots of the appellant before the Consolidation Authorities. Their claims are pending companysideration in revisions under s. 48 of the Consolidation Act.
